cs.DL, cs.SI, cs.CY, cs.IR, cs.SD 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as it deals with the analysis of citation data. Additionally, it could also belong to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it involves the study of gender differences in academia. Other possible sub-categories include cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it deals with gender inequalities, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it involves the analysis of large datasets, and cs.SD (Software Engineering) as it involves the development of algorithms for data analysis.
